President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his Administration. Shannon Lee Goessling of Florida is nominated to be the Director of the Office of Violence Against Women at the Department of Justice. She has a successful legal and business career, serving as a prosecutor, businesswoman, non-profit executive, and chief legal counsel. She has advocated for victims of domestic violence and other crimes and has founded two small businesses.

Daniel Simmons of Virginia is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary for Energy, Efficiency, and Renewable Energy at the Department of Energy. He has served as the Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Office of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy, overseeing technology development in the energy efficiency and renewable power sectors.

Irving Bailey of Florida is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. He is nominated for a remainder of a three-year term expiring in December 2018 and an additional three-year term expiring in December 2021.